# Cursor Rules — Sakir Saiyed Portfolio

You are working on a React 18 + Vite 6 personal portfolio website.

## Key Principles

1. **Data-driven content**: All text content lives in `src/data/siteData.js`. Never hardcode strings in JSX.
2. **Vanilla CSS only**: No Tailwind, no CSS-in-JS. Each component has a co-located `.css` file.
3. **CSS variables for theming**: Always use `var(--token-name)` from `src/styles/tokens.css`. Never hardcode colors.
4. **Path aliases**: Use `@components`, `@sections`, `@hooks`, `@data`, `@styles`, `@assets`. Never use relative paths.
5. **Functional components**: Default exports. Use hooks from `@hooks` (useTheme, useScrollReveal).
6. **Section pattern**: Every section gets `useScrollReveal()` ref, `.section` class, `.container` wrapper, `.reveal` children.
7. **BEM-ish naming**: `.block__element`, `.block--modifier` (e.g., `.hero__content`, `.btn--primary`).

## When editing sections

- Import data from `@data/siteData`
- Use `<span className="section-label">` → `<h2 className="section-title">` → `<p className="section-subtitle">` pattern
- Apply `.reveal` and `.reveal-delay-{1,2,3}` classes for scroll animations
- Alternate sections use `className="section section--alt"` for the secondary background

## When editing styles

- Define in the section's co-located `.css` file
- Use CSS variables from tokens.css for all colors, fonts, spacing
- Mobile breakpoint: `@media (max-width: 768px)`
- Card pattern: `background: var(--bg-card)`, `border: 1px solid var(--border)`, `border-radius: 14-16px`
- Hover pattern: `border-color: var(--border-hover)`, `transform: translateY(-2px)`, `box-shadow: var(--shadow-card-hover)`
- Transition pattern: `transition: all 0.3s var(--ease-out-expo)`

## Fonts

- Headings: `var(--font-display)` — Inter
- Body: `var(--font-body)` — Inter
- Code/labels: `var(--font-mono)` — Fira Code

## Icons

- UI icons: `import { IconName } from 'lucide-react'`
- Brand icons: `import { GithubIcon, LinkedInIcon, MediumIcon } from '@components/Icons'`

## Don't

- Don't install Tailwind, React Router, SASS, or CSS-in-JS libraries
- Don't use class components
- Don't put content strings directly in JSX
- Don't use relative imports (../../)
- Don't use localStorage outside of useTheme hook
